  {title: "Avengers Academy (2010) #34", modified: "2014-03-05T12:35:58-0500", issue_number: 34, marvel_id: 40258, image_path: "http://i.annihil.us/u/prod/marvel/i/mg/d/60/58e5000367824/portrait_uncanny.jpg", description: "AvX fall-out: Avengers Academy is closed...indefinitely! Alchemist, a.k.a. wunderkind industrialist Jeremy Briggs, offers the students a chance to be normal again! But is there a catch? And who will accept his deal?"},
  {title: "Agents of Atlas (Hardcover)", modified: "2016-02-03T10:26:16-0500", issue_number: 0, marvel_id: 6318, image_path: "http://i.annihil.us/u/prod/marvel/i/mg/b/f0/4bc354467aacc/portrait_uncanny.jpg", description: "The spy. The spaceman. The goddess. The robot. The gorilla. During the late 1950s, the U.S. government allowed FBI Special Agent Jimmy Woo to forge a team of unlikely heroes. Together, they stormed the fortress of a criminal mastermind to rescue President Eisenhower ' but the group disbanded soon after. Now, almost 50 years later, an unauthorized S.H.I.E.L.D. mission goes down in flames ' and from the ashes arise forces from the Golden Age of Marvel! Collecting AGENTS OF ATLAS #1-6 ' plus the Agents' first appearances in stories from YELLOW CLAW #1 (Jimmy Woo; October 1956), MENACE #11 (Human Robot; May 1954), VENUS #1 (August 1948), MARVEL MYSTERY COMICS #82 (Namora; May 1947), MARVEL BOY #1 (December 1950), MEN'S ADVENTURES #26 (Gorilla Man; March 1954) and WHAT IF? #9 (1950s Avengers; June 1978). Also featuring blogs, creator interviews, character designs and other extras!\r\n256 PGS./Rated T  '$24.99"},
  {title: "Agents of Atlas (2009) #1", modified: "2015-11-06T14:27:00-0500", issue_number: 1, marvel_id: 23659, image_path: "http://i.annihil.us/u/prod/marvel/i/mg/f/a0/563cfef44cc7b/portrait_uncanny.jpg", description: ""},
  {title: "Agents of Atlas (2009) #2", modified: "2015-11-06T14:27:44-0500", issue_number: 2, marvel_id: 23825, image_path: "http://i.annihil.us/u/prod/marvel/i/mg/9/30/563cff212b1f7/portrait_uncanny.jpg", description: "Norman Osborn's shadow government looks to pull ahead in the arms race with the help of the Atlas Foundation and the\r\nUranian weaponry of the world's most bizarre defense contractor, Marvel Boy! The dark contacts grow even more solid when Jimmy Woo meets his understudy - Temujin, the son of the Mandarin! How does this all connect to one of the Agents' 1958 missions? Access M-11's datahold and find out!\r\nRated T  ...$2.99"},
  {title: "Agents of Atlas (2009) #2 (BACHALO 2ND PRINTING VARIANT)", modified: "-0001-11-30T00:00:00-0500", issue_number: 2, marvel_id: 27402, image_path: "http://i.annihil.us/u/prod/marvel/i/mg/2/60/4bb4e5edf3b8c/portrait_uncanny.jpg", description: nil},
  {title: "Agents of Atlas (2009) #2 (MCGUINNESS VARIANT)", modified: "-0001-11-30T00:00:00-0500", issue_number: 2, marvel_id: 23824, image_path: "http://i.annihil.us/u/prod/marvel/i/mg/9/d0/4bb5981d5dd57/portrait_uncanny.jpg", description: "Norman Osborn's shadow government looks to pull ahead in the arms race with the help of the Atlas Foundation and the\r\nUranian weaponry of the world's most bizarre defense contractor, Marvel Boy! The dark contacts grow even more solid when Jimmy Woo meets his understudy - Temujin, the son of the Mandarin! How does this all connect to one of the Agents' 1958 missions? Access M-11's datahold and find out!\r\nRated T  ...$2.99"},
  {title: "Agents of Atlas (2009) #3", modified: "2015-11-06T14:26:20-0500", issue_number: 3, marvel_id: 24015, image_path: "http://i.annihil.us/u/prod/marvel/i/mg/f/60/563cfecd1dd36/portrait_uncanny.jpg", description: "Back in the 1950's our heroes fall deeper into the mystery of the Dragon's Corridor- leading them to Communist plots and two mysteriously familiar bodies on ice. In the present day, a similar trail of intrigue winds back to secret plans of the Atlas Foundation. The Agents look to be building a hellish arsenal for Norman Osborn, and they've just gotten the attention of none other than CAPTAIN AMERICA!\r\nParental Advisory ...$2.99"},
  {title: "Agents of Atlas (2006) #4", modified: "-0001-11-30T00:00:00-0500", issue_number: 4, marvel_id: 5404, image_path: "http://i.annihil.us/u/prod/marvel/i/mg/2/90/56b21a3540a64/portrait_uncanny.jpg", description: "\"Most of us don't realize when we're experiencing pivotal history...Today I did. I knew I was witnessing the return of a legend. \" \r<br>- S.H.I.E.L.D. Subdirector Derek Khanata, from his report \r<br>on NAMORA. \r<br>The Sea Monarch joins the AGENTS OF ATLAS as they take on an evil that looks to be deeper than the ocean itself!\r<br>32 PGS./Rated T+ ...$2.99\r<br>"},
  {title: "Agents of Atlas (2006) #5", modified: "-0001-11-30T00:00:00-0500", issue_number: 5, marvel_id: 5665, image_path: "http://i.annihil.us/u/prod/marvel/i/mg/8/b0/56b21add1851b/portrait_uncanny.jpg", description: "Revelations show one of the team to be a double agent, and another something more horrific than their enemies. The Atomic Age alliance crumbles as the team has its own Civil War. The time to test the leadership of Jimmy Woo is here. \r<br>32 PGS./Rated T+ ...$2.99\r<br>"},
  {title: "Agents of Atlas (2009) #6", modified: "2015-11-06T14:36:14-0500", issue_number: 6, marvel_id: 24360, image_path: "http://i.annihil.us/u/prod/marvel/i/mg/9/50/563d011f4fff4/portrait_uncanny.jpg", description: "Disturbing visions plucked from the malignant mind of Norman Osborn lead the intrepid Agents to the darkest depths of the Atlantic Ocean, where Namora must have words with her infamous cousin - The Sub-Mariner! What happens next shocks her team, who must prepare to say goodbye to their aquatic avenger!\r\nRated T  ...$2.99"},
  {title: "Avengers 1959 (2011) #1", modified: "2011-09-30T16:27:07-0400", issue_number: 1, marvel_id: 40360, image_path: "http://i.annihil.us/u/prod/marvel/i/mg/8/30/4e80d0fb2b010/portrait_uncanny.jpg", description: "EXPLODING FROM THE PAGES OF NEW AVENGERS... It's the tail end of the fabulous fifties.  NICK FURY and his AVENGERS roar into their secret mission, hunting down NAZI SUPER VILLAINS...men and women relentlessly preparing to unleash hell on a troubled world barely holding onto peace...only to find the Avengers have what appears to be serious competition in their manhunt for these escaped ubermenschen...when their mission is suddenly compromised by interference from an unlikely source."},
