  {title: "Deadpool & the Mercs for Money (2016) #1", modified: "2016-07-15T15:20:05-0400", issue_number: 1, marvel_id: 59963, image_path: "http://i.annihil.us/u/prod/marvel/i/mg/6/e0/578d104bb799c/portrait_uncanny.jpg", description: "Deadpool is one of the best mercenaries on the planet. He may even be a passable Avenger—jury’s still out. But one thing’s for sure—Deadpool is a terrible team leader. Think we’re lying? Ask the Mercs for Money! Deadpool’s taken on a new high-paying mission to take out radioactive super villains...and his Mercs aren’t nearly as immune to radiation as his healing-factored heinie is. Deadpool veteran Cullen Bunn brings us mo’ mercs, mo’ money and naturally, mo’ problems."},
  {title: "Deadpool & the Mercs for Money (2016) #2", modified: "2016-08-05T11:52:57-0400", issue_number: 2, marvel_id: 59964, image_path: "http://i.annihil.us/u/prod/marvel/i/mg/4/10/57a365838b55f/portrait_uncanny.jpg", description: "The Mercs for Money have taken down Negasonic Teenage Warhead…but maybe that wasn’t such a good thing to do? And if they didn’t like HER vibes…wait ‘til they take on Radioactive Man!"},
  {title: "Deadpool & the Mercs for Money (2016) #3", modified: "2016-09-01T10:53:47-0400", issue_number: 3, marvel_id: 59965, image_path: "http://i.annihil.us/u/prod/marvel/i/mg/3/a0/57c59455260db/portrait_uncanny.jpg", description: "The Mercs have spoken—Deadpool sucks! At being their leader, I mean! Deadpool is still awesome. Please keep buying his comics."},
