  {title: "Howard the Duck (1979) #5", modified: "-0001-11-30T00:00:00-0500", issue_number: 5, marvel_id: 21091, image_path: "http://i.annihil.us/u/prod/marvel/i/mg/b/40/image_not_available/portrait_uncanny.jpg", description: nil},
  {title: "Hulk Vs. Dracula (2011) #1", modified: "2015-11-12T12:35:34-0500", issue_number: 1, marvel_id: 39751, image_path: "http://i.annihil.us/u/prod/marvel/i/mg/6/c0/4e68d41703fe6/portrait_uncanny.jpg", description: "FEAR ITSELF TIE-IN\nAs the possessed, power-enhanced Hulk wreaks havoc through the countryside, only one group stands between him and untold destruction: The Vampire Nation! Dracula gathers the newly-united vampire legions to stop the unstoppable, but as volley after volley fails, it appears their only hope may be a mysterious stranger from Dracula's past. Marvel craftsman Victor Gischler and artist-to-watch Ryan Stegman deliver a story with plenty of bite, and they aren't afraid to draw blood!"},
