  {title: "Astonishing Tales (1970) #25", modified: "2016-09-27T18:02:44-0400", issue_number: 25, marvel_id: 43414, image_path: "http://i.annihil.us/u/prod/marvel/i/mg/3/c0/57c88c5a55333/portrait_uncanny.jpg", description: "Behold! The birth of the cyborg known as Deathlok! Military strategist Col. Luther Manning loses his humanity in a post-apocalyptic science experiment. Now, trapped in an amalgam of flesh and circuitry, Deathlok lives between life and death, man and robot."},
  {title: "Astonishing Tales (1970) #26", modified: "2017-01-25T14:38:14-0500", issue_number: 26, marvel_id: 43424, image_path: "http://i.annihil.us/u/prod/marvel/i/mg/5/04/57c88cf7cbec8/portrait_uncanny.jpg", description: "One of the first adventures of Deathlok the Demolisher! Deathlok, now a “Death Machine for Hire”, goes after his first victim. But what does Simon Ryker have in store for Deathlok after his first kill?"},
  {title: "Astonishing Tales (1970) #27", modified: "2016-09-27T18:10:19-0400", issue_number: 27, marvel_id: 43423, image_path: "http://i.annihil.us/u/prod/marvel/i/mg/a/80/57c88d9c671fd/portrait_uncanny.jpg", description: "Deathlok takes on War-Wolf! In a future where warfare is accomplished through genetically modified soldiers, will Deathlok prove the supreme “super soldier” of them all? Plus, who was War-Wolf before his transformation, and what ties does he have to Deathlok’s past?"},
  {title: "Astonishing Tales (1970) #28", modified: "2016-09-27T18:10:28-0400", issue_number: 28, marvel_id: 43422, image_path: "http://i.annihil.us/u/prod/marvel/i/mg/d/10/57c98d81ebce4/portrait_uncanny.jpg", description: "Deathlok wanders far from the land he calls home to find Simon Ryker and kill him. However, Ryker is able to foresee Deathlok’s arrival and sends out armored tanks to defeat his creation-gone-rogue."},
  {title: "Astonishing Tales (1970) #30", modified: "2016-09-27T18:11:00-0400", issue_number: 30, marvel_id: 43420, image_path: "http://i.annihil.us/u/prod/marvel/i/mg/6/d0/57c98c2d148e1/portrait_uncanny.jpg", description: "Deathlok continues to battle Ryker’s men, but meets a true foe in a massive tank powered by Nina’s mind. Meanwhile, Mike Travers escapes his cell and continues his hunt for Deathlok."},
  {title: "Astonishing Tales (1970) #31", modified: "2016-09-27T18:11:16-0400", issue_number: 31, marvel_id: 43425, image_path: "http://i.annihil.us/u/prod/marvel/i/mg/a/60/57c98b66d8ce3/portrait_uncanny.jpg", description: "Mike Travers and Deathlok meet face-to-face! Deathlok discovers that Travers, aka War-Wolf, married his wife six months ago. Enraged, Deathlok is about to kill the man when he remembers the time War-Wolf spared his life. Deathlok continues his hunt for Ryker, but the surgeon has called in help from the mob. Will Deathlok find the revenge he desperately longs for?"},
  {title: "Astonishing Tales (1970) #32", modified: "2016-09-27T18:11:26-0400", issue_number: 32, marvel_id: 43419, image_path: "http://i.annihil.us/u/prod/marvel/i/mg/9/90/57c98a2feb161/portrait_uncanny.jpg", description: "Knowing that Col. Ryker has ties to the mob, Deathlok shoots down a helicopter transporting a mobster who may have pertinent information. Will Deathlok’s trail run dry when the mob man swears to protect Ryker’s whereabouts?"},
  {title: "Astonishing Tales (1970) #33", modified: "2016-09-27T18:11:35-0400", issue_number: 33, marvel_id: 43415, image_path: "http://i.annihil.us/u/prod/marvel/i/mg/7/90/57c98939b2e7c/portrait_uncanny.jpg", description: "The hunt for Ryker ends here! See Deathlok’s rampage of revenge in “Reflections in a Crimson Eye!”"},
  {title: "Astonishing Tales (1970) #34", modified: "2016-09-27T18:11:43-0400", issue_number: 34, marvel_id: 43416, image_path: "http://i.annihil.us/u/prod/marvel/i/mg/1/20/57c9884800a93/portrait_uncanny.jpg", description: "After failing to detach an explosive on his wrist, Deathlok loses his bionic arm and much of his body. Mike Travers, anti-hero, manages to retrieve Deathlok’s body from the blast and takes him to the C.I.A for tinkering. There, Deathlok is re-programmed with one mission operative; take down Simon Ryker once and for all. Ryker re-invents himself as the half-cyborg, Savior Machine."},
  {title: "Astonishing Tales (1970) #35", modified: "2016-09-27T18:11:53-0400", issue_number: 35, marvel_id: 43418, image_path: "http://i.annihil.us/u/prod/marvel/i/mg/a/70/57c9869de0c5f/portrait_uncanny.jpg", description: "Deathlok discovers a way to switch his mind and body with Simon Ryker. Driven to madness in Deathlok’s body, Ryker is no longer a threat. With Ryker destroyed, Deathlok accepts a new mission from the C.I.A. But will Luther Manning lose his humanity as he continues to be a weapon-for-hire?"},
  {title: "Astonishing Tales (1970) #36", modified: "2016-09-27T18:12:01-0400", issue_number: 36, marvel_id: 43417, image_path: "http://i.annihil.us/u/prod/marvel/i/mg/a/50/57c985cd54ae9/portrait_uncanny.jpg", description: "Deathlok is hired by the C.I.A to eliminate a threat from Hellinger. During the mission, Deathlok discovers clones of Luther Manning, and must destroy each incarnation of himself!"},
  {title: "Avengers Arena (2012) #2", modified: "2014-03-05T12:30:34-0500", issue_number: 2, marvel_id: 44677, image_path: "http://i.annihil.us/u/prod/marvel/i/mg/6/e0/58cc31928ef53/portrait_uncanny.jpg", description: "- ANNIHILATION's Cammi vs. Deathlocket!\n- AVENGER ACADEMY's Hazmat vs. Deathlocket!\n- Who the heck is Deathlocket? And who dies in this issue?\n- Plus: Who are the students of the Braddock Academy?"},
  {title: "Avengers Arena (2012) #4", modified: "2014-03-05T12:31:00-0500", issue_number: 4, marvel_id: 45859, image_path: "http://i.annihil.us/u/prod/marvel/i/mg/9/b0/58cc45549afb3/portrait_uncanny.jpg", description: "The Runaways vs. Avengers Academy!"},
  {title: "Captain America (1968) #286", modified: "2017-08-25T12:30:26-0400", issue_number: 286, marvel_id: 7667, image_path: "http://i.annihil.us/u/prod/marvel/i/mg/9/50/50ad71950aef8/portrait_uncanny.jpg", description: nil},
  {title: "Captain America (1968) #287", modified: "2017-08-25T12:34:09-0400", issue_number: 287, marvel_id: 7668, image_path: "http://i.annihil.us/u/prod/marvel/i/mg/6/00/59a051220eb9f/portrait_uncanny.jpg", description: nil},
  {title: "Captain America (1968) #288", modified: "2017-08-25T12:35:12-0400", issue_number: 288, marvel_id: 7669, image_path: "http://i.annihil.us/u/prod/marvel/i/mg/e/d0/50ad70fed0ad7/portrait_uncanny.jpg", description: nil},
  {title: "Deathlok (2009) #1", modified: "2013-03-06T09:05:16-0500", issue_number: 1, marvel_id: 24967, image_path: "http://i.annihil.us/u/prod/marvel/i/mg/6/90/51b5f741d339f/portrait_uncanny.jpg", description: "Marvel's ultimate cyborg is back in this 7-issue Marvel Knights limited series written by Charlie Huston (MOON KNIGHT) and breathtakingly illustrated by Lan Medina (FOOLKILLER).\r\nIn the not-too-distant future, war is a spectator sport, warriors die hard and live fast, and living larger than anyone is super-soldier Lieutenant Mike Travers.  That is, until Travers hotdogs it on the battlefield and gets himself and his C.O., Luther Manning, blown to bits.  The show must go on.  Enter: Deathlok the Demolisher!!!\r\nParental Advisory ...$3.99"},
  {title: "Deathlok (1990) #1", modified: "2016-10-07T14:07:40-0400", issue_number: 1, marvel_id: 48303, image_path: "http://i.annihil.us/u/prod/marvel/i/mg/a/a0/57d6bf8e675d8/portrait_uncanny.jpg", description: "Witness the creation of a new Deathlok! Will he be a hero or a villain?"},
  {title: "Avengers (1963) #55", modified: "2015-09-15T13:54:13-0400", issue_number: 55, marvel_id: 7305, image_path: "http://i.annihil.us/u/prod/marvel/i/mg/c/a0/4e96fbc1e4a29/portrait_uncanny.jpg", description: nil},
  {title: "Avengers (2010) #1", modified: "2017-11-02T12:36:35-0400", issue_number: 1, marvel_id: 29195, image_path: "http://i.annihil.us/u/prod/marvel/i/mg/5/d0/5a26b363b12d7/portrait_uncanny.jpg", description: "Kang The Conqueror has come from the future! Now, The Avengers must assemble to prevent a catastrophic threat from tearing apart the timestream. But who will answer the call?"},
  {title: "Avengers (2010) #1 (I AM AN AVENGER BLANK COVER VARIANT)", modified: "2017-12-05T10:18:03-0500", issue_number: 1, marvel_id: 33572, image_path: "http://i.annihil.us/u/prod/marvel/i/mg/2/20/4bed7bcda35c6/portrait_uncanny.jpg", description: "THE HEROIC AGE IS HERE!\r\nThere came a day! A day unlike any other...where two of Marvel's top creators teamed up for the very first time to create a bombastic new monthly Marvel comic that not only ushers in the Heroic Age of Marvel Comics but unleashes onto the world the most blockbuster Avengers team ever! Who will answer the call?  And will they assemble just in time...because Kang the Conqueror is here from the future. And wait till you find out why...! Bonus back up feature:  the oral history of the Avengers, part one. A brand new illustrated look at the Avengers in a way you have never seen before by series writer Brian Michael Bendis.\r\nRated A"},
